    <bioghist>Edward Allen was a professor of mathematics at the University of Michigan (1915-1919) later Iowa State University. He and his wife Minne were both active in peace causes. Their son Julius was an economist with the Library of Congress.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Letters of Minne and Edward Allen, of their son Julius W. Allen, and of other members of Muller-Allen family. Include letters of Minne Muller Allen to her mother, 1894-1919 (in German with translations); letters exchanged between Julius W. Allen and his parents, 1931-1981.</scopecontent>
